# Planning and design docs

## Single source of truth

All architecture and operator docs live in committed repo files:

- **Entry:** [`docs/usage.md`](docs/usage.md) (pipeline map, GitHub and local commands)
- **Block 1:** [`docs/mirror-init.md`](docs/mirror-init.md) (`yarn mirror-init`; [Tooling branch layout](docs/mirror-init.md#tooling-branch-layout))
- **Block 2:** [`docs/mirror-poll.md`](docs/mirror-poll.md) (`yarn mirror-poll`)
- **Block 3:** [`docs/mirror-sync.md`](docs/mirror-sync.md) (CI on mirror repos)
- **Block 4:** [`docs/mirror-merge.md`](docs/mirror-merge.md) (`yarn mirror-merge`; replay algorithm)

Edit the doc that matches the area you are changing. Do not create other parallel
plan files unless the user explicitly asks.

## Do not use Cursor internal plans

Do **not** treat Cursor's internal plan feature as the project plan:

- No authoring or updating `~/.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` as the canonical design
- No copying plans to/from Cursor-only paths instead of the repo
- No "save to repo later" -- changes belong in `docs/` in the same turn

## When design changes

1. Update [`docs/usage.md`](docs/usage.md) when pipeline map, repos, CI boundaries, or operator flows change
2. Update the matching block doc (`mirror-init.md`, `mirror-poll.md`, `mirror-sync.md`, `mirror-merge.md`) for block-specific detail
3. Commit plan changes when the user asks (or as part of an agreed docs pass)
4. Reference these paths in code, rules, and PRs -- not Cursor plan URLs

## Agent behavior

- Read design from committed docs, not from conversation-only or Cursor-internal state
- Start from [`usage.md`](docs/usage.md) for pipeline and operator flows
- Block detail: `mirror-init.md`, `mirror-poll.md`, `mirror-sync.md`, `mirror-merge.md`
- If committed docs and chat history disagree, the committed files win unless the user is actively revising them
